quran[29]{c,v,t}:
  27,27,"He said, ´We will soon see if you have told the truth or are a liar"
  27,28,Take this letter of mine and deliver it to them and then withdraw from them a little and see how they respond.´
  27,29,"She said, ´Council! a noble letter has been delivered to me"
  27,30,"It is from Sulayman and says: \"In the name of Allah, All-Merciful, Most Merciful"
  27,31,"Do not rise up against me, but come to me in submission.\"´"
  27,32,"She said, ´Council! give me your opinion about this matter. It is not my habit to make a final decision until I have heard what you have to say.´"
  27,33,"They said, ´We possess strength and we possess great force. But the matter is in your hands so consider what you command.´"
  27,34,"She said, ´When kings enter a city, they lay waste to it and make its mightiest inhabitants the most abased. That is what they too will do"
  27,35,I will send them a gift and then wait and see what the messengers bring back.´
  27,36,"When it reached Sulayman he said, ´Would you give me wealth when what Allah has given me is better than what He has given you? No, rather it is you who delight in your gift"
  27,37,Return to them. We will come to them with troops they cannot face and we will expel them from it abased and humiliated.´
  27,38,"He said, ´Council! who among you will bring me her throne before they come to me in submission?´"
  27,39,"An ifreet of the jinn said, ´I will bring it to you before you get up from your seat. I am strong and trustworthy enough to do it.´"
  27,40,"He who possessed knowledge of the Book said, ´I will bring it to you before your glance returns to you.´ And when he saw it standing firmly in his presence, he said, ´This is part of my Lord´s favour to test me to see if I will give thanks or show ingratitude. Whoever gives thanks only does so to his own gain. Whoever is ungrateful, my Lord is Rich Beyond Need, Generous.´"
  27,41,"He said, ´Disguise her throne. We shall see whether she is guided or someone who is not guided.´"
  27,42,"Then when she came, she was asked, ´Is your throne like this?´ She said, ´It is exactly like it.´ ´We were given knowledge before her and were already Muslims"
  27,43,but what she worshipped besides Allah impeded her. She was from an unbelieving people.´
  27,44,"She was told: ´Enter the courtyard,´ but when she saw it she supposed it to be a pool and bared her legs. He said, ´It is a courtyard paved with glass.´ She said, ´My Lord, I have wronged myself but I have submitted with Sulayman to the Lord of all the worlds.´"
  27,45,"To Thamud We sent their brother Salih telling them to worship Allah, and straightaway they divided in two, arguing with one another"
  27,46,"He said, ´My people, why are you so anxious to hasten the bad before the good? If only you would ask for forgiveness from Allah, so that mercy might perhaps be shown to you.´"
  27,47,"They said, ´We see you, and those with you, as an evil omen.´ He said, ´No, your evil omen is with Allah; you are merely a people undergoing a trial.´"
  27,48,There was a group of nine men in the city causing corruption in the land and not putting things right
  27,49,"They said, ´Let us make an oath to one another by Allah that we will fall on him and his family in the night and then say to his protector, \"We did not witness the destruction of his family and we are telling the truth.\"´"
  27,50,They hatched a plot and We hatched a plot while they were not aware
  27,51,So look at the end result of all their plotting; We utterly destroyed them and their whole people
  27,52,These are the ruins of their houses because of the wrong they did. There is certainly a Sign in that for people with knowledge
  27,53,We rescued those who had iman and who had taqwa
  27,54,"And when Lut said to his people: ´Do you approach depravity with open eyes"
  27,55,Do you come with lust to men instead of women? You are a people who are deeply ignorant.´